posts.name: Sam Mulvey
posts.cooked: Hi all! My robot code has been having on and off trouble building and pushing to the robot. I have no errors in the actual code (Java) and sometimes it will say build failed because of an error code of 1 with compileJava. It tells me to check the code for errors and make sure every file is saved. I am sure the code is fine because after a few hours or so, or when something on my laptop updates or changes, the problem disappeared. Restarting my laptop / hard power cycling does not fix the issue. I have also reinstalled Java and that hasn’t helped. Any ideas?

posts.name: Gavin Matthews
posts.cooked:
It would help a lot to see a screenshot or photo of the error message, but some things to check might be:

roboRIO updated to latest version

Code using latest version of wpilib

Connected to robot

JAVA_HOME set correctly

Try clearing Gradle cache

Disable Window firewall

posts.name: Brad
posts.cooked:
Sometimes intellisense gets turned off or deactivated and compile errors don’t show in the code editors.   We have this problem on the student computers where the code is on onedrive. (The school default config)

If you do a build robot code and it fails the terminal tab should have information on what happened

posts.name: Peter Johnson
posts.cooked: Definitely make sure your project is not on OneDrive, as that can cause all sorts of strange issues.  It could also be a computer problem (eg bad memory).

posts.name: Sam Mulvey
posts.cooked: Any suggestions for tests I can run on the laptop to diagnose that kind of issue?

posts.name: Peter Johnson
posts.cooked: MemTest86 is the original self booting memory testing software for x86 and ARM computers. Supporting both BIOS and UEFI, with options to boot from USB.
